	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-29T04:34:18">3i Group plc is a United Kingdom-based investment manager focused on mid-market private equity, infrastructure and debt management. The Company invests in northern Europe and North America markets. The Company provides investment to private equities in various sectors, such as consumer, industrial and business services. The Company provides investment to utilities, transportation and social infrastructure in the United Kingdom and Europe. The Company's debt management is a fund management business, which generates returns through managing third-party capital through collateralized loan obligations (CLOs) and other senior debt focused funds. The Company's debt management includes management of funds, which invest in senior and mezzanine corporate debt in various companies in the United Kingdom, Europe and North America.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-27T14:40:42">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, 3i Group plc revenues decreased 19% to L269M. Net income decreased 39% to L155M. Revenues reflect Quoted Private Equity segment decrease of 13% to L246M. Net income also reflects FV Adjustments of Financial Investments increase from L10M (income) to L31M (expense), Carried interest and performance fees re increase from L19M (income) to L10M (expense). Dividend per share remained flat at L0.06.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
